bio.experienceSummary: Hi there! My name is Gia, and I am passionate about providing children with a safe, fun, and nurturing environment. As a babysitter, I understand the importance of not only ensuring your child's safety but also contributing to their growth and happiness. I have a solid background in childcare, having babysat for several families over the past 3 years. Through my experience, I've cared for children of all ages, from infants to pre-teens, and have developed a strong understanding of their needs at every stage of development. What sets me apart is my personality. I am patient, compassionate, and highly responsible. My goal is to create a balance between fun and structure, ensuring your child is entertained. If you're looking for a babysitter who is not only responsible but also warm, energetic, and truly enjoys spending time with children, I'd love to help out. I look forward to the opportunity to care for your little ones and create a positive experience for both them and you!

I grew up in a big family both immediate and extended. I am the oldest of seven and I have been surrounded by babies/young children my entire life. I also babysit at school. I have been with that family for almost two years now and continue to have a good relationship with them. I am trustworthy, responsible, and reliable.

description.displayText: Kayleigh has been our babysitter for the past 4 years.  My kids love it when she watches them because she is fun, plays games with them and has even taken them out to dinner. We have had such a great experience with Kayleigh. She is reliable and responsible and a great role model. We are lucky to have her and your family would be too.

bio.experienceSummary: I've been helping with children since I was teenager. I had 5 siblings and I was oldest. My duties included watching children, helping with them as mother, taking care my own children, now teenagers. I'll provide references if requested.

I am a nurturing and responsible 20-year-old mom with extensive hands-on childcare experience.
Naturally compassionate and highly dependable, I combine personal insight with professional skills to
create a safe, engaging, and enriching environment for children. My patience, creativity, and love for nurturing young minds makes me an excellent choice for a nanny role.

I believe in open communication with parents and will provide regular updates on your child's day, using your preferred method of communication. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules to ensure a safe and structured environment.

From outdoor sports and physical games to board games and puzzles, I enjoy a wide range of activities that promote learning and fun. I'm confident that I can provide your children with a stimulating and enjoyable experience.

I have a car, am comfortable with pets, and am CPR and First Aid certified.

I love kids and kids love me! I have a lot of experience babysitting and nannying for families with children of all ages. I have had experience working at a daycare center in the preschool and infant rooms. I have also worked as a camp counselor for over 5 years at various performing arts camps and programs, and interned as an English TA at a high school in Vienna, Austria. The children I work with love me because am just as fun and imaginative as they are. Here is a poem one of my 12 yr old Austrian students wrote for me: Singer, Active, Much Fun, Always happy, Natural, Theater, Honest.

I am looking for a part time nanny position with consistent hours that work with my grad school schedule.

Starting in May or June (possibly sooner), I will be available to work full days Wednesday-Friday.

description.originalText: Sam has been caring for our daughter since she was 7 months old (she is now 2!) and has been so wonderful. She is gentle, sweet, caring, and attentive. She drives my daughter weekly to classes and is always careful and cautious. She handles meltdowns and tantrums with calmness and ease, which is especially helpful for the big feelings our 2 year old has. She has been such a help to our family.

bio.experienceSummary: Positive, calm, balanced, committed, ambitious, compassionate, reliable, kind and very creative. My 2 daughters are my highest achievement making me proud every single day. In the past I worked as a Art teacher for kids with disabilities at "Special School Sacel" Romania. Between 2000 and 2005 I was part of an amazing French nonprofit organization "L'École de clown" where I was doing art therapy with homeless kids. I am in the process of getting a degree in Art Therapy so I could use my creative skills to help kids and adults to express themselves through art. I am very patient, caring and nurturing person, highly skilled in educational activities to stimulate physical, social and cognitive development of the child. I have also worked for many years as a baby sitter and floating lead teacher in daycare setting. Babysit children between 1 month to 10 years old. Recently I received my certification for CPR, First Aid and AED.

description.displayText:
I am writing to express my recommendation for Camelia M. Cami has worked as a babysitter for my two year old toddler for the last 9 months. She serves as an excellent role model to my young child. My daughter always looked forward to her time with Cami and are always very sad to see her leave. She used to do lot of great art work and read her books and teach her lessons of life. 
She is a very kind and responsible person. She has never given me reason to believe that she could not handle any situation that was put before her. You would be very fortunate to hire her as an employee

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as patient, friendly, caring 

I like working with kids because I have a passion for watching children develop and grow and make those milestones it's very rewarding . I also just graduated with a degree in elementary education. 

I started working with kids when I was 18

In my spare time, I like to read , travel and try new foods . 

One thing you should know about me is I'm
Very respectful towards families and am very patient with children of all ages . Ranging from infants to teens .

My skills include planning and scheduling as well as over 4 years experience working with children. Diaper changing, feeding, house work, and child development

Hello, my name is Gillian. I am 23 years old and CPR certified! My experiences include but are not limited to working at a daycare for 3 years, babysitting long-term for several families with children ranging from infants to pre-teens, teaching a before and after school program in the Warren public school system, working for a company called Baby Bandstand which required me to teach musical/speech pathology classes for children 6-18 months, teaching for several dance companies, teaching at the YMCA, and most recently working for 2. 5 years with two children. I started when they were 4 years and 3 months and they are now 6 years and 2. 5 years. If you think I might be a good fit for your family you can reach me through care. com. I hope to hear from you soon! Thanks for your consideration!

I'm an experienced childcare provider with a passion for nurturing and educating children. I've been caring for kids for over nine years, and I'm comfortable looking after up to four children of all ages. I've worked with families from a variety of backgrounds and have experience with children of all ages, from infants to preteens.

I believe that every child is unique and deserves to be treated with respect and compassion. I'm patient, calm, and creative, and I love coming up with fun and educational activities for children. I'm also very comfortable enforcing household rules and routines. I believe that clear expectations are essential for creating a safe and nurturing environment for children.

I'm confident that I can provide your family with reliable and high-quality childcare. I'm available to discuss your needs and answer any questions you may have. I look forward to hearing from you!

Hello, 
My name is Shalayne. I am a 38-year-old woman who has been around kids for all of my life. Growing up with 4 younger siblings, I was pretty much my mother's helper with everything. I have been in the child care business for the better side of 20 years working with ages from infant to 20 years old. I was also a preschool teacher for 2years and a ABA para professional for 4 years in NJ. I would love to meet with you to see if we are a great fit for each other. Thank you for taking the time out and reading my application. Hope to hear from you soon and have an amazing day.

description.originalText: Shalayne is a dedicated and a giving person with children. She goes above and beyond. She also has great communication with parents, which is very important when it comes to this kind of work. I highly recommend Shalayne. To top it off, she has tons of experience and is aware of children’s cognitive abilities and development.
